  "title": "Principal C&S Engineer / Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>Brown Consulting Pte. Ltd. is an independent civil & structural engineering consultant. For over 25 years, we have been providing professional engineering consulting services and solutions to meet the most stringent requirements from many large scale infrastructure and architectural projects.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Coordinate and lead civil and structural engineering design projects by preparing documentation, managing client and authority relationships, and guiding engineering teams to deliver quality outcomes within budget and schedule.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate and prepare comprehensive design documentation for civil and structural engineering projects to meet technical and regulatory standards</li><li>Develop and maintain collaborative relationships with internal teams and external clients to facilitate project success</li><li>Liaise effectively with local authorities to secure design approvals and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements</li><li>Lead, develop, train, and support engineering staff to enhance team capabilities and project delivery</li><li>Budget and allocate time and costs accurately to fulfill technical requirements of project briefs</li><li>Adhere to project quality system requirements as outlined in the Project Quality Plan and promptly report any non-conformances to the Project Lead with recommended corrective actions</li><li>Demonstrate problem-solving skills to achieve project goals and resolve conflicts amid competing priorities</li><li>Implement performance measurement systems to drive continuous improvement and enhance service delivery</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s or Master’s Degree in Civil or Structural Engineering</li><li>Professional Engineer (PE) Certificate is desirable</li><li>Proficient in design software and knowledgeable in relevant design standards</li><li>Experienced with local engineering practices and technical requirements</li></ul>",
